{"word":"πιφαύσκω","slug":"πιφαύσκω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>πιφαύσκω</b></el> <el>(πι-φαύσκω,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:reduplication'>redupl.</a> form of <el>ΦΑ</el>, Root of <a href='S:φαίνω'><el>φαίνω</el></a>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>only in <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a> and <a href='S:imperfect tense'>imperf.</a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to make manifest, declare, tell of</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>: <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, <el>πιφαύσκων Διομήδεϊ</el> <i>making signal</i> to him, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to set forth</i> words, <i>utter</i>, <el>μῦθον, ἔπεα</el> <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> et <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to tell</i> one to do, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> <i>to make manifest</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; <i>to tell of, disclose</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}